# Pirate Memory Game — Core Constraints

A static HTML5 point-and-click pirate memory game in Hebrew (RTL).

## Concept

Player sees a treasure map with visual memory clues for a configurable time (default 10s).
Wind blows the map away (cannot be reopened). Player sails between randomized islands.
Each island character asks a 4-choice question based on one map clue. Correct → next island.
Wrong → island-specific lose screen with progress. All islands cleared → win screen.

## Hard constraints (NEVER violate)

- Static HTML site only. No backend, server, database, npm, build step, bundler, or framework.
- No React, Vue, Angular, Vite, Next.js, or TypeScript.
- Only `index.html`, CSS, vanilla JavaScript, and static assets.
- Must run by opening `index.html` directly via `file://`.
- Must also work on GitHub Pages / any static host.
- Do NOT use `fetch()` for local JSON (breaks `file://`). Store game data in `.js` files.

## File structure (do not over-engineer)

```
index.html
css/style.css
js/config.js      # CONFIG settings
js/riddles.js     # RIDDLES pool
js/utils.js       # shuffle, helpers
js/renderer.js    # DOM rendering
js/gameState.js   # state + transitions
js/main.js        # wiring / entry
README.md
```

Prefer clear functions with meaningful names. Avoid complex abstractions. Keep it
understandable for a WEB course assignment. Separate config, riddle data, state,
rendering, and utilities.
